{"section": "3.12.1: Using strong induction.", "qid": 2, "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n <p>\n  Suppose that the inductive step of a strong induction proof shows that for k \u2265 1, if (S(0) \u2227 S(1) \u2227 .... \u2227 S(k)) is true, then S(k+1) is true.\n </p>\n</div>\n", "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <div class=\"setup flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"label\">\n   3)\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"text\">\n   If you assume that the inductive hypothesis is true, can you conclude that S(k-1) is true?\n  </div>\n </div>\n <fieldset>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember94\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"Yes\" name=\"13\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember93&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    Yes\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember96\">\n   <input aria-label=\"No\" name=\"13\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember95&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    No\n   </label>\n  </div>\n </fieldset>\n</div>\n", "choices": ["<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember94\">\n <input aria-label=\"Yes\" name=\"13\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember93&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  Yes\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember96\">\n <input aria-label=\"No\" name=\"13\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember95&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  No\n </label>\n</div>\n"], "answer": "Yes", "explanation": "<div aria-atomic=\"true\" class=\"explanation has-explanation correct\" role=\"alert\">\n <p class=\"message\">\n  Correct\n </p>\n Since k \u2265 1, then k-1  \u2265 0. Therefore k-1 falls in the range from 0 through k and  the inductive hypothesis includes the assumption that S(k-1) is true.\n</div>\n"}